1
00:00:11,416 --> 00:00:13,625
[HARUHIKO] Urban redevelopment
is a waste of resources

2
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,083
that no one asked for.

3
00:00:15,166 --> 00:00:18,166
As residents of the
Kokorogaoka Housing complex,

4
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:21,166
we refuse to leave our homes
for the sake of nothing.

5
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:24,250
We proclaim the entire complex,
from Building A to Building H,

6
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:26,291
to be named the
"Kokogaoka Borough".

7
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:27,791
And, as of this moment,

8
00:00:27,875 --> 00:00:31,458
we declare our independence
from the nation of Japan.

9
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:33,875
The government
will respect this.

10
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:35,916
[YOSHIO grunts]

11
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,083
Hey.

12
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,500
Thank you for your time.
And take care now.

13
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,583
[KENSUKE]
Haru.

14
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:45,708
Hey!

15
00:00:45,791 --> 00:00:47,458
[KENSUKE growls]

16
00:00:47,541 --> 00:00:48,708
[YOSHIO]
Uh!

17
00:00:51,416 --> 00:00:52,541
Tsk.

18
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:57,500
[KENSUKE pants]

19
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:04,250
[KENSUKE pants]

20
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:11,416
[KENSUKE grunts, shouts]

21
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:13,083
[grunts]

22
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:20,666
[KENSUKE wimpers]

23
00:01:34,875 --> 00:01:36,541
[KENSUKE]
Haruhiko.

24
00:01:40,583 --> 00:01:44,208
[AKECHI] So, this isn't the
first time he's cheated on you?

25
00:01:44,291 --> 00:01:45,750
[WOMAN A]
That's right.

26
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:49,666
[AKECHI] Makes sense, sadly.
Affairs can be like cockroaches.

27
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:51,958
If you find one,
it's probably safe to assume

28
00:01:52,041 --> 00:01:53,708
there are about a dozen more.

29
00:01:53,791 --> 00:01:54,458
[KENSUKE]
Boss!

30
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:55,166
[gasps]

31
00:01:55,250 --> 00:02:00,208
[pants]

32
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:05,458
Please. Help... me.

33
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:10,500
♪

34
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:38,666
Hey. How's it hanging, kiddo?

35
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,916
[KENSUKE pants]
You saw the news, right?

36
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,375
[AKECHI] Huh? You mean
the stuff about me?

37
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:45,958
[KENSUKE] This is no time
to just be sitting around!

38
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:47,333
There's a client here!

39
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:49,041
If we don't hurry, Haru will--

40
00:03:49,125 --> 00:03:49,958
Forget it.

41
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:51,291
[gasps]

42
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:53,083
[AKECHI] If there's no pay,
I'm not interested.

43
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,916
Huh?!

44
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,833
We're trying to
conduct business.

45
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:57,958
Be quiet.

46
00:03:58,041 --> 00:03:59,833
[KENSUKE grunts]

47
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:01,083
[WOMAN A]
Uh, well...

48
00:04:01,166 --> 00:04:03,416
Sorry. We'll happily
take your case.

49
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,000
[WOMAN A]
Huh?

50
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:07,291
[NORO] We'll call you as soon
the investigation is complete.

51
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:09,833
Take care, now.

52
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,666
[WOMAN A]
Thanks. You, as well.

53
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,208
Alright, you're clear.

54
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:20,250
[KENSUKE grunts] This is no
time to be playing around!

55
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:23,791
I'm sick of doing nothing.
Of seeing bad things happen

56
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:26,583
and accepting it
instead of fixing it!

57
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:29,166
[KENSUKE grunts]

58
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:31,333
Detectives aren't heroes,
Kensuke.

59
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:32,875
[KENSUKE]
But my brother.

60
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:34,541
[AKECHI]
I won't say it again.

61
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,791
[KENSUKE]
Fine. I'll go to Nakamura.

62
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:37,750
[AKECHI]
Hanasaki!

63
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:39,000
[gasps]

64
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:44,583
[AKECHI exhales]
If you do that, you're done.

65
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:46,041
[KENSUKE]
You think I care?

66
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:47,458
[INOUE]
Chill, Hanasaki.

67
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:50,125
[NORO]
Seriously. You need to relax!

68
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:51,750
I don't understand, boss.

69
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,583
You take jobs
without being hired.

70
00:04:54,666 --> 00:04:56,375
[AKECHI] You aren't
allowed to leave today.

71
00:04:56,458 --> 00:04:57,416
[gasps]

72
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,750
[AKECHI]
No going out.

73
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:00,458
You can't do that!

74
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:03,666
You know the rules.
In this place, my word is law.

75
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:08,125
[KENSUKE growls]
Dammit! What's your problem?

76
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:09,916
[door hums]

77
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,916
[YOSHIO] There you are.
Thanks for ditching me.

78
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:16,000
[KENSUKE exhales]

79
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,833
[INOUE] Just where do
you think you're going?

80
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:23,458
Up to the roof.

81
00:05:28,375 --> 00:05:29,500
Hey.

82
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,041
Quit ignoring me.

83
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:38,791
Man. I'm exhausted.
Helluva first day back.

84
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:41,375
Think I'll take the
rest of the day off.

85
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:46,541
It isn't over. You can't
just leave it like that.

86
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,291
[grunts]

87
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:51,458
I said everything that
was on my mind.

88
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:53,666
[INOUE] Don't sleep
and eat. It's not healthy.

89
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,791
My office. I'll do
what I want here.

90
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,000
[doorbell rings]

91
00:05:57,083 --> 00:05:59,041
Another one. Be a dear
and get that for me.

92
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,708
You've got two legs of your own.

93
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:08,541
[gasps]

94
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,875
[NORO] Maybe we should
just throw it away.

95
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:13,750
What if it's C4 or something?

96
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:18,791
[AKECHI] Relax. Even if it is,
it won't kill Yoshio.

97
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:21,625
[INOUE]
True. But it will kill us.

98
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:24,250
[NORO]
How are you both so calm?!

99
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,291
Huh?

100
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,666
That's strange.

101
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:28,291
What is it?

102
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:29,333
[gasps]

103
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:32,500
A toy? Creepy.

104
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:34,625
Actually, it's a coin bank.

105
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:36,083
[INOUE]
Hm?

106
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:38,375
[TWENTY-FACES] I found a new
playground for us, Akechi.

107
00:06:38,458 --> 00:06:41,541
How does the Kokorogaoka
Housing Complex sound?

108
00:06:41,625 --> 00:06:42,250
[PIPPO hoots]

109
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,791
[NORO]
Isn't that?

110
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:45,666
[TWENTY-FACES] You should
bring your new toy out to play.

111
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:48,833
After all this time, you must
be tired of the old one.

112
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:50,333
I know I am.

113
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:51,791
[toy clatters]

114
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:57,375
[AKECHI] Like I said,
It isn't a damn toy.

115
00:06:57,458 --> 00:06:59,083
[YOSHIO]
What the hell are you doing?

116
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:00,583
[INOUE]
Sit there and be quiet.

117
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:01,500
[AKECHI]
Kobayashi.

118
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:02,625
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

119
00:07:02,708 --> 00:07:05,041
I need you to do
something for me.

120
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:06,291
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

121
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,333
[KENSUKE grunts]

122
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:11,458
[YOSHIO]
Hey.

123
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:13,500
[KENSUKE gasps]

124
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:14,833
Where are you going?

125
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:15,875
[KENSUKE]
For a walk.

126
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:16,750
[YOSHIO]

127
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,583
[KENSUKE gasps]

128
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:20,333
[YOSHIO]
What? I'm coming with you.

129
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,083
[KENSUKE]
I know what this is.

130
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:24,916
Akechi asked you to babysit me.

131
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,416
[gasps]
How did you know?

132
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:30,541
[KENSUKE] When did you get
so attached to him, anyway?

133
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:31,791
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

134
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:34,833
[KENSUKE grunts]
Just leave me alone, alright?

135
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:35,750
[YOSHIO]
Really?

136
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:36,500
[gasps]

137
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:38,083
Don't flatter yourself.

138
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,333
[gasps]

139
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:41,875
[YOSHIO] I don't care
about you. Never have.

140
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:42,583
[gasps]

141
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:44,000
Will it kill me?

142
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:45,125
[KENSUKE]
What?

143
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:47,833
Tsk. I know you're
working a case, man.

144
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:50,833
It's obvious. Is it dangerous?

145
00:07:50,916 --> 00:07:52,333
Could I die?

146
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:54,625
Just give up on that for today.

147
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:58,125
What? Like hell I will.
You promised!

148
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,375
You said you'd kill me. Do it!

149
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:04,083
Dammit. I've got bigger
things to worry about!

150
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:09,166
[INOUE]
Why did you let him leave?

151
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,375
Huh?

152
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:13,000
You were told to watch him!
Did you forget?

153
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:14,166
[YOSHIO]
I did watch him.

154
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,958
Don't split hairs with me!

155
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:18,333
You're so annoying.

156
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:19,541
Excuse me?

157
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:21,958
[YOSHIO] Your life is
your responsibility.

158
00:08:22,041 --> 00:08:23,500
Isn't that the first rule?

159
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,083
[gasps]

160
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:28,458
[AKECHI] Well I'll be damned.
One of you actually listened.

161
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:30,500
[NORO]
I'll have Pippo follow Hanasaki.

162
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:31,291
No need.

163
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:32,500
[PIPPO hoots]

164
00:08:34,208 --> 00:08:37,625
Guess we wait.
Hopefully they'll call soon.

165
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:43,291
Seriously, boss? How long
can a damn date last?

166
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:45,375
[BOSS A]
Miyanishi, are you listening?

167
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,625
Yes! Sorry!

168
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:49,041
Those idiots made one
hell of a mess for us.

169
00:08:49,125 --> 00:08:50,500
We can't afford
to be complacent

170
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:52,166
after he hijacked
a public broadcast.

171
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,541
Do you know anything
about this housing complex?

172
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:55,916
Of course we do!

173
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,291
It's impossible not to
notice the wall they built.

174
00:08:58,375 --> 00:09:00,750
If they'd just stayed
quietly barricaded inside,

175
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,208
we could've overlooked this.

176
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:03,750
[BOSS C]
Any new demands from them?

177
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,416
They're keeping quiet.

178
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,250
[BOSS D] Force is an option,
but that's a PR nightmare.

179
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,291
[BOSS C]
This shouldn't be our concern.

180
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,125
[BOSS D] What choice do we have?
All the bureau's are

181
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:15,250
short-staffed after
the robot incident.

182
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:17,750
What if we sent in a
recon team, for now?

183
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,041
That's better than
twiddling our thumbs.

184
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:23,416
C'mon. What the hell
are you doing, boss?

185
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,708
We need you.

186
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:37,833
Quite the uniform. Is that
what you're like on the job?

187
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:40,000
It's even better. Heh.

188
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,750
[phone rings]

189
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:48,666
Hey, what's up?

190
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:51,458
Yeah, I called.
Is dad still there?

191
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:54,333
Of course he's not.
You saw the news right?

192
00:09:54,416 --> 00:09:55,625
Haru is--

193
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:01,083
[KENSUKE]
No, Akashi, listen!

194
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:04,875
[KENSUKE grunts]
Fine. Forget it!

195
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:11,000
[HARUHIKO]
Please stop crying.

196
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:15,708
[KENSUKE sobs]
I can't do it. I can't ride.

197
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:17,000
[HARUHIKO]
Did it hurt?

198
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:18,083
[KENSUKE]
Uh-huh.

199
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:21,125
[HARUHIKO]
I see. But, you know what?

200
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,125
That pain is proof you're alive,
and makes you stronger.

201
00:10:24,208 --> 00:10:26,208
[KENSUKE]
Really?

202
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,750
[HARUHIKO]
Think of it this way;

203
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:31,000
All superheroes power-up by
overcoming pain and suffering.

204
00:10:31,083 --> 00:10:33,875
Then, if I get stronger,
will it make you happier, too?

205
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:35,125
[HARUHIKO]
Sure.

206
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:36,625
What about dad?

207
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:38,000
[HARUHIKO]
Of course.

208
00:10:38,083 --> 00:10:39,708
[KENSUKE gasps]

209
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,916
[HARUHIKO]
Hey. What's all this about?

210
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,750
[KENSUKE] If I get stronger, can
I stay in this house forever?

211
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,125
[HARUHIKO]
Kensuke...

212
00:10:47,208 --> 00:10:51,125
[KENSUKE sniffs] I don't
wanna move again! I hate it!

213
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:54,000
You don't have to worry
about that anymore.

214
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:55,541
[KENSUKE]
Really?

215
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:59,041
Yeah. That's a promise
from big brother.

216
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:09,708
[sighs]
What the hell?

217
00:11:28,916 --> 00:11:30,208
[KENSUKE grunts]

218
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:41,458
[SERVANT A] Did you hear
about the national mock exams?

219
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:43,875
[SERVANT B]
I did! Isn't it amazing?

220
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,416
Those boys have some
incredibly gifted minds!

221
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,375
[SERVANT A] Apparently,
Haruhiko has already started

222
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:50,625
to help his father with
business ventures.

223
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:51,875
[SERVANT B]
Already?

224
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:54,375
The master's certainly
not wasting any time.

225
00:11:54,458 --> 00:11:57,375
[SERVANT A] I guess the
Hanasaki's future is secure.

226
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:03,333
[KENSUKE gasps]

227
00:12:04,708 --> 00:12:05,875
[KENSUKE]
Hm.

228
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:09,750
[KENSUKE grunts]

229
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,958
How can you say something
so cruel about your son?

230
00:12:13,041 --> 00:12:16,750
You can't just throw
Kensuke out like garbage!

231
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:17,916
[KENSUKE gasps]

232
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,708
This had already been
decided when we

233
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:21,666
first brought you two here.

234
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,791
I've arranged things
with the orphanage.

235
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:24,875
You can't.

236
00:12:24,958 --> 00:12:26,083
[KENSUKE'S DAD]
Kensuke is insurance.

237
00:12:26,166 --> 00:12:27,333
Father!

238
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:29,375
You should just focus
on your own happiness.

239
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,541
He isn't even your
blood relative.

240
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:35,666
He's still... my brother.
Blood doesn't matter!

241
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,500
Haruhiko.

242
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,583
[grunts]

243
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:45,666
[KENSUKE gasps]

244
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:47,291
[HARUHIKO]
You finally awake?

245
00:12:47,375 --> 00:12:48,208
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

246
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,791
[HARUHIKO]
It's been awhile.

247
00:12:49,875 --> 00:12:50,833
[KENSUKE]
Big brother?

248
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:51,666
[HARUHIKO]
Kensuke.

249
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,000
[KENSUKE gasps]
It is you!

250
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,166
[HARUHIKO gasps]
You've grown a lot, haven't you?

251
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:58,291
[KENSUKE] Mm. What have you
been doing all these years?

252
00:12:58,375 --> 00:13:00,916
I... I...

253
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,583
[HARUHIKO] I see you're still
good at waterworks, huh?

254
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:04,708
[KENSUKE grunts]
Whatever, I wasn't crying.

255
00:13:04,791 --> 00:13:05,541
[HARUHIKO]
Let's go.

256
00:13:05,625 --> 00:13:06,666
[KENSUKE]
Uh?

257
00:13:08,041 --> 00:13:11,541
[HARUHIKO] There's so much
to see... In my country.

258
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:26,916
[KENSUKE]
Mm?

259
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:32,708
Oh. Those are ID tags.

260
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:34,041
For what?

261
00:13:34,125 --> 00:13:37,708
They identify them as my family.
You have one, too.

262
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:39,750
[KENSUKE]
Mm? When'd you do that?

263
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,083
Ah-ah! Don't touch it.

264
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:43,875
Take it off, you die.

265
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:45,125
[KENSUKE gasps]

266
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:48,250
Let's keep going.
I'll introduce you to mom.

267
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,541
Uh...

268
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,083
[PIPPO hoots]

269
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:54,916
[NORO]
Can we really just let this go?

270
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,333
He's an adrenaline junkie!

271
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:58,916
Who knows what mess
he'll get into.

272
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,833
[INOUE] The boss said
not to do anything.

273
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:03,958
[NORO] Don't any of you care
what happens to Hanasaki?

274
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:05,833
[INOUE]
Quit shouting.

275
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:08,083
[NORO] We should at least
take that stupid robot toy

276
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:10,625
Twenty-Faces sent
us to the police.

277
00:14:10,708 --> 00:14:12,250
We'll decide how
to handle everything,

278
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,916
--including that, without them.
--[glass rattles]

279
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:19,958
[AKECHI grunts, sighs]
What the hell was that?

280
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:21,500
Kobayashi.

281
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:24,500
[YOSHIO] Leave him alone.
He'll come back if he wants to.

282
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:26,833
The kids got a point.

283
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,291
[grunts]

284
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:34,833
[KENSUKE]
Use this to find my brother.

285
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:36,458
I told you, I can't.

286
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:37,458
[KENSUKE]
If it's not enough,

287
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:39,041
I'll work until
I've paid it off.

288
00:14:39,125 --> 00:14:40,583
Please, help me!

289
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:43,708
[AKECHI] Sorry, kid.
I'm just not feelin' this one.

290
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:45,125
[KENSUKE gasps]

291
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:07,333
Ambushing me like this
is in pretty poor taste.

292
00:15:07,416 --> 00:15:07,916
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

293
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:08,958
[AKECHI]
Here.

294
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:11,166
Hold on.

295
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:12,666
[AKECHI]
Eh?

296
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,916
I looked everywhere I can
think of and couldn't find him.

297
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,625
I'm worried about
my big brother.

298
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,250
I'm not the one you
should ask, kid.

299
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,291
Go to your parents.

300
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:21,875
He won't help me!

301
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:24,250
My dad doesn't care
that Haru is gone.

302
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,625
That's why I'm doing this!

303
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:29,708
I see. That's a
tough break, kid.

304
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:30,916
[KENSUKE gasps]

305
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:35,708
It'll be dark soon.
You should head on home.

306
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:46,666
There you are.

307
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,208
[ISUZU]
Hm?

308
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:52,666
[HARUHIKO]
I brought him like you asked.

309
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,208
Good work, son.

310
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,666
Well, Kensuke, what do you
think of the place so far?

311
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,666
Huh?

312
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:04,791
The country that
Haru and I built.

313
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:06,416
I just want him
to leave with me.

314
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,625
And why should he do that?

315
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:10,083
It's not like he's
done anything wrong.

316
00:16:11,541 --> 00:16:13,625
We've all worked hard
to build a life here.

317
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,708
We won't let it be taken away.

318
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:16,958
The residents are family

319
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,416
and we'll protect
them with our lives.

320
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,916
Protect them?

321
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,750
Look, Kensuke. Every one of
them have had a rough past.

322
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,333
[HARUHIKO] And all of them
found their way here

323
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,250
by depending on mom.

324
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,208
This place is a second
chance for them.

325
00:16:29,291 --> 00:16:31,875
If they're run out, they'll
return to their former lives.

326
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:34,750
Okay, but how long do you
think you can keep all this up?

327
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:36,333
For as long as it takes.

328
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:38,750
We've set up countermeasures
to ensure that.

329
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:39,750
Meaning?

330
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:40,958
Show him, please.

331
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,291
[HARUHIKO]
Yes, mother.

332
00:16:44,791 --> 00:16:45,583
I'm sorry.

333
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:46,416
For what?

334
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,958
[helicpoter hums]

335
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:50,000
[ISUZU]
Well, that was perfect timing.

336
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:52,541
[KENSUKE gasps]

337
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:53,958
--Watch closely, young man.
--[KENSUKE] Huh?

338
00:16:54,041 --> 00:16:55,875
[alarm buzzes]

339
00:16:55,958 --> 00:16:57,833
[ANNOUNCER] Warning.
Entering the yellow zone

340
00:16:57,916 --> 00:16:59,250
is strictly forbidden to any

341
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:01,916
who are not citizens
of this borough.

342
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,125
Entering the yellow zone
is strictly forbidden

343
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:07,083
to any who are not
citizens of this borough.

344
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:08,541
It's coming.

345
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:19,916
What the hell are you doing?
Don't shoot at the police!

346
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,541
Relax, okay? They're just
in the yellow zone.

347
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,041
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

348
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:27,500
[ANNOUNCER] This is a warning.
Repeat: This is a warning.

349
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:32,291
If you pass into the red zone,
we cannot guarantee your safety.

350
00:17:32,375 --> 00:17:34,666
[HARUHIKO] When anyone
without a tag comes near us,

351
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:38,250
sensors detect them and the
defense system activates.

352
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,166
[ISUZU]
That's our countermeasure.

353
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:42,375
If they still want
to die like dogs,

354
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:44,041
they're welcome
to come back.

355
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:46,958
This is our country and it's
going to stay that way.

356
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:48,000
Look, you--

357
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:49,250
[grunts]

358
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:51,500
[HARUHIKO] We only want
to protect our family.

359
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:53,375
[KENSUKE grunts]

360
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:55,750
[HARUHIKO] I know you
understand that, Kensuke.

361
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:01,916
[KENSUKE gasps]

362
00:18:06,791 --> 00:18:11,250
[HARUHIKO] Kensuke.
You really like dad, don't you?

363
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:17,416
You'd like to stay
here forever, if you could.

364
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:21,083
Don't you worry.
I'll make sure that happens.

365
00:18:25,958 --> 00:18:30,916
[KENSUKE grunts]

366
00:18:36,541 --> 00:18:37,916
[gasps]

367
00:18:40,583 --> 00:18:43,333
[KENSUKE gasps]

368
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:50,708
[KENSUKE]
Wait, Haru!

369
00:18:52,791 --> 00:18:56,083
[KENSUKE]
Haru? Where you'd go?

370
00:18:56,166 --> 00:19:01,125
[pants]

371
00:19:05,166 --> 00:19:06,833
Who're you, brat?

372
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:09,458
[gasps]
Sorry. I was mistaken.

373
00:19:09,541 --> 00:19:10,125
[BUYER A]
Hold up.

374
00:19:10,208 --> 00:19:11,625
[KENSUKE shouts]

375
00:19:11,708 --> 00:19:13,750
Those are nice clothes.
Where'd you get'em?

376
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:14,791
Let me go!

377
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:17,416
Gotta rich daddy, kid?

378
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:20,916
[DEALER A] Check it.
He's got electronic-cash!

379
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,166
Give it back!

380
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,291
Help! Help!

381
00:19:24,375 --> 00:19:27,250
Shut your mouth! Annoying brat!

382
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,541
[gasps]

383
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:31,291
Beating up on a child, man?
That's some hobby.

384
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:32,833
[DEALER A]
Who are you?

385
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:36,000
My name's worth more than punks
like you could ever afford.

386
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:37,541
Oh yeah?

387
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:42,625
Now, then. Let's get you home.

388
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:47,625
It's gonna take at least an hour
to get there this time of day.

389
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,916
I hope you don't have a
curfew or anything, kiddo.

390
00:19:52,416 --> 00:19:54,666
Don't do that.
If someone sees us,

391
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:57,250
they'll think I'm being
mean to you or something.

392
00:19:57,333 --> 00:20:01,250
[KENSUKE] Haru was talking to
my dad before he disappeared.

393
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,791
[AKECHI]
Hm?

394
00:20:02,875 --> 00:20:05,625
[KENSUKE sobs] Dad told him to
think of his own happiness.

395
00:20:05,708 --> 00:20:06,625
So why?

396
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:08,291
[AKECHI]
Well. If I had to guess,

397
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:11,333
I'd say that leaving home was
what would make him happy.

398
00:20:11,416 --> 00:20:13,958
[KENSUKE]
Haru is the one dad picked...

399
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:17,791
...but because I said
I wanted to stay, he--

400
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:20,083
Wow. I had it wrong, kid.

401
00:20:20,166 --> 00:20:23,000
Protecting you is what
made him truly happy.

402
00:20:23,083 --> 00:20:26,125
That's a pretty cool
brother you got there.

403
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:28,208
If you still want to
look for him after today,

404
00:20:28,291 --> 00:20:30,916
I won't try to stop you,

405
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,333
but you'd better become a
man he can be proud of first.

406
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:38,291
Now, come on.
I'll take you home.

407
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:39,458
Uh?

408
00:20:39,541 --> 00:20:42,541
[KENSUKE grunts]
I want... to get stronger.

409
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:44,166
[AKECHI gasps]

410
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:46,708
[KENSUKE] But I don't
know how to do that.

411
00:20:46,791 --> 00:20:49,958
Please teach me to be a man!
For my brother!

412
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:51,666
[sobs]

413
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,000
[AKECHI gasps]

414
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:54,958
[HARUHIKO]
Kensuke.

415
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:56,208
[KENSUKE]
Yeah?

416
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,166
[HARUHIKO]
We can be together as family.

417
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:01,125
Would you like that?

418
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:02,625
Haru, I...

419
00:21:02,708 --> 00:21:05,458
[HARUHIKO] Our country has
everything we could ever need.

420
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:08,750
I can make you happy, the way
your so-called friends couldn't.

421
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,125
[gasps]

422
00:21:15,416 --> 00:21:16,791
A representative
from the borough

423
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,291
just called
the main office!

424
00:21:18,375 --> 00:21:19,708
[ALL gasp]

425
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,541
[NAKAMURA]
Hm.

426
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:27,416
[phone buzzes]

427
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:28,708
[NAKAMURA grunts]

428
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:31,458
[phone rings]

429
00:21:31,541 --> 00:21:34,708
[AKECHI] Hello.
Akechi Investigation Firm.

430
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:37,166
[AKECHI chuckles]
Took you long enough, idiot.

431
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:38,291
[phones clatters]

432
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:44,958
"Kay. Let's give Hanasaki
a piece of our minds.

433
00:21:45,041 --> 00:21:46,041
[YOSHIO]
Hm.

434
00:21:46,416 --> 00:21:51,375
♪

435
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:40,416
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Fallen Hero."

